{
  "stem": "4289.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And sometimes in nightgowns, we were to run out, just to save our own flesh and blood because he was crazy.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He even fed his horses with alcohol, a dog that ran away later.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "One day he put me in a barn with a horse that was drunk-- because he gave him alcohol-- and left me there overnight.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And your mother, the adoptive mother, did not have any defenses against him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No she was really afraid of him, because he was the one who supported us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had a wife, which he did not respect.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know for what reason, but I think the most he was punishing his wife.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my mother saw the situation, and just to get away from this drunkard, she took me with her on trains.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We took a luggage, and many times, whatever was possible to find, we would take on the train, like cigarettes, tobacco, alcohol.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we would sell it in the train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And many times, when times were really, really bad, my mother used to put half alcohol, half water, seal it with wax and put a little penny on it so it will look like it was never touched.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we sold it on the trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But eventually, people would recognize us, so we had to change the routes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my mother never gave up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We still did the same thing over and over because if not, we wouldn't be able to eat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had, there were times when my mother, and I went through the neighbor's garbage and picked up the peels from the garbage to cook them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I have to mention that my mother was really a just person.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Whatever she gave her daughter, she gave the same to me.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
